    "The table 5 represents a weighted normalized decision matrix, which combines normalized performance data with assigned weights (from Table 4) to evaluate multiple criteria in a decision-making context.",
    "Each value in the matrix is the product of the corresponding normalized metric and its weight (0.25).",
    "This approach ensures that the final values reflect both the relative performance of each metric and its importance in the evaluation process.",
    "For example, the first row shows moderate values across all metrics, with efficiency of resource utilization scoring 0.086786 and energy consumption at 0.087584.",
    "These values indicate balanced performance with no extremes."
